-- Russian Steelmaker Severstal Acquires a 25.6% Stake in South Africa's IBMS
-- B y   R o n   D e r b y
-- 2010-10-01T07:07:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-01/severstal-buys-25-6-stake-in-south-africa-s-iron-mineral-for-17-million.html
OAO Severstal, Russia’s largest
steelmaker, has bought a 25.6 percent stake in South Africa’s
Iron Mineral Beneficiation Services for $17 million, IMBS said
in a statement distributed in Johannesburg today.  Severstal will help IMBS build a plant in Phalaborwa, the
company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ron Derby in Johannesburg at 
